      • createArithmetic

        public static Factory createArithmetic​(java.lang.String name,
                                       ArithmeticOperator.ArithmeticOperationI iOp,
                                       ArithmeticOperator.ArithmeticOperationF fOp)
        Creates an operator factory instance suitable for registering with the Parser.

        An operator factory is used to create expression instances for a given operator and set of operands. e.g. 

        
   Factory f = Operators.createArithmetic("+", (l, r) -> l + r, (l, r) -> l + r);
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the operator
        iOp - the operator function for integer values
        fOp - the operator function for floating point values
        Returns:
        a Factory instance for creating arithmetic expressions for inserting into the expression tree

      • toBoolean

        public static boolean toBoolean​(java.lang.Object value)
        Converts an expression result to a binary true/false value.

        The general rule is that non-zero numbers and strings with a non-zero legth are true. Zero, null, and empty strings are false. Boolean values are returned as is.

        Parameters:
        value - the value to convert to boolean
        Returns:
        true or false depending upon the value

      • in

        public static java.lang.Boolean in​(java.lang.Object left,
                                   java.lang.Object right)
                            throws ExpressionError
        Value in list operator.

        This provides an 'in' operator (similar to that in Python) used for determining whether or not a value exists in a list.

        Parameters:
        left - the value to search the list for
        right - the list to search
        Returns:
        true if the value exists in the list, false otherwise
        Throws:
        ExpressionError - if the list is not valid
